title: Bug 114470[Smoke] Error message throws when using new Date("3/2/2005") as value in table filter.
description: When trying to use the JavaScript function new Date("3/2/2005") as a value in a table filter, an error message is thrown.
OB: When using new Date("3/2/2005") as a value in a table filter, an error message is thrown.
EB: The table filter should accept new Date("3/2/2005") as a valid value without throwing any error message.
SR: Steps to reproduce: 1. Open the table filter. 2. Enter new Date("3/2/2005") as a value. 3. Observe the error message being thrown.
